name: Ritz Classic-Panjim Gymkhana

reviews.review_text:
Being a Sunday the place was quite full, but we got seats immediately.
we reached late so no thali was available.
We ordered A La Carte...food was good.
Service was lousy, prawns curry was deliicious , so was sukha teesryo, prawns hakka noodles quantity  was quite less.our fried fish came after we finished our food.
Took 15 minutes to get water and for finger bowls.
Extremely bad service.

This is a nice place by the Panjim Miramar road with a lot of free inhouse parking services. The restaurant provides both AC and non AC sections. The ambience is good in AC as well as the breezy non-AC section. I preferred the cool natural breezy area. I tried the squid golden fry, chonaak rava fry which was fresh and crispy. Among the drinks, Cinderella was very sweet having only the taste of the slice.The gimlet was good but the quantity was very less.  One must try the chicken 65 at this place which has a good taste. Coriander chicken is nice and yummy, a must try here. The service is great here. The waiters are very polite and welcoming. Overall a good place to visit with family or friends.

•Trip type: Dinner with Friends

•Service: 3.0

•Location: 3.5

•Hotel highlights: Nice place suited for family & friends.

•Walkability: No walking distance; it's Just on the road with good enough inhouse free parking.

Went for Sunday lunch.
This "multi-cuisine " restaurant is more famous for its Goan cuisine, so suggest stick to that.
It has totally ~300 covers, 140 in ac section (most prefered), 40 in Alfresco, & 150 outdoors along Promenade.
Starters:
Prawn Dangar (cutlets) - most disappointing in both Presentation & taste - suggest pl Avoid!.
Butter garlic squids - good.
Entrée: "Kurylo" (crab) butter garlic - excellent in taste, & VFM @Rs 580.
Kingfish thali- v good.
Service was attentive.
Note: Indoors ac gets full by 1.15pm, so go early.
Would strongly recommend this place for good Goan cuisine, in a decent ambiance.

description:
## Restaurant Review: Ritz Classic-Panjim Gymkhana

Nestled along the breezy Miramar road in Panaji, **Ritz Classic-Panjim Gymkhana** boasts a commendable rating of **4.2** stars from **5,900 reviews**. Diners have frequently highlighted its signature offerings, especially the **thali**, prominent **Goan** cuisine, and a delightful experience by the **poolside**—elements that intertwine to create a memorable dining destination.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon arrival, guests are greeted by a charming yet vibrant atmosphere, which balances a rustic coastal charm with modern comfort. The restaurant features both an air-conditioned and a non-AC section, with the non-AC area providing a refreshing natural breeze that many patrons prefer. The overall décor creates a warm and inviting space, perfect for families and friends alike. Numerous customer-uploaded photos showcase intimate table settings, cheerful staff, and a stylishly understated design that accommodates around 300 diners—140 in the air-conditioned section and generous outdoor seating. 

Customers have noted the lively ambiance, especially during peak hours like Sundays, where the place buzzes with energy, reflective of its ever-increasing popularity.

![Ambiance](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdkc6KjSpjmNLmREGj_iFHnO43xAK9eCYze2QCt5-jA41wO8GTxQU8CqT9is6KYrpF0X0pOUwxCa2mrNriWN855s-Fejoj0YPcAZ87jXrY0PcsONLlKV9Fa0HDizJQdP7KMiYKeS=w375-h281-p)

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu is a delightful exploration of **multi-cuisine** options but is best known for its **Goan** specialties. Reviewers recommend sticking to Goan cuisine for the best experience. Signature dishes such as the **Kingfish thali** and the **Kurylo (crab) butter garlic** have received rave reviews for their exceptional flavors and value, with the latter priced at a reasonable ₹580. Customer favorites also include **Butter Garlic Squids**, **Chicken 65**, and crispy **Chonaak Rava Fry**, which are reported to be refreshingly appetizing.

Patrons have experienced a mix of presentation styles, with some starters like the prawn cutlets disappointing in both appearance and taste, while main courses generally impress. Overall, the food showcases a vibrant presentation that tantalizes the appetite.

![Food Presentation](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdm-mmb-xKIF-rhjTDE28ToIkTW4SQ5f9F2Sm9AGNio_m4TCX9lje11vVA9dA306jiwnCT_NEsrzrJUx18-M9BwPO0P_nKnIKkmf3IRaD6O_C6OfIakLEWgmHMUvVnPsnL8rgkfckg=w375-h281-p)

### Customer Experience & Service

While the culinary offerings shine, the service experience has drawn mixed reviews. Some diners report prompt and attentive service, particularly for dine-in experiences. However, others have noted considerable delays—waiting 15 minutes for basic items like water and finger bowls, which dampens the overall experience. Nevertheless, the waitstaff have generally been described as polite and welcoming, contributing to a comfortable atmosphere for group dining.

Reservations may be advisable, especially during busy times, as the air-conditioned section fills up quickly—advised by one reviewer to arrive early.

### Popularity & Reviews

The restaurant enjoys considerable social media buzz, with patrons continuously sharing their experiences and favorite dishes. Its strong emphasis on **Goan** cuisine, bolstered by a solid reputation, positions Ritz Classic as a must-visit culinary haven in Panaji. With accolades from diners highlighting its value for money and ambiance, this venue consistently attracts local and visiting food enthusiasts.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The vibrant and mouthwatering food visuals eloquently captured by diners showcase the restaurant’s character—from the colorful thalis to the enticing seafood dishes. Each image reflects the care put into food preparation and plate presentation, promising a feast for the eyes before the palate.

![Seafood Dishes](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdkfZRFNgiQD3vDguyPGdFoxevQ_kKowrPYcc4LlFID5dxW8DWKg9GTluIOgwZhImFSZStDRenMZ-tpymZWlBOb_b51fmu9afeqOoZZQy5PdJkShXWN--MnMIjV0I68qIKOfZLXVAw=w375-h281-p)

In conclusion, Ritz Classic-Panjim Gymkhana presents an enticing blend of **Goan** cuisine, a lively atmosphere, and picturesque surroundings—making it a worthwhile destination for diners seeking both cultural vibrancy and delightful flavors in the heart of Panaji.
